text: Pisces-Eridanus stellar stream is a close stellar stream 80-226 parsecs away from Earth. It is estimated to be only 120 million years old, similar age to the Pleiades. It is estimated this stellar stream contains about 1400 stars and has a solar mass of 770 M\odot. == Stars == The stream includes at least 6 visible stars: Lambda Tauri, Omicron Aquarii, 106 Aquarii, Tau1 Aquarii and Nu Fornacis.
title: Pisces-Eridanus stellar stream
